Okay, careful. Walk carefully.

1205
01:11:52,391 --> 01:11:54,893
We need to ban
partial-birth abortions. I believe

1206
01:11:54,977 --> 01:11:57,146
banning partial-birth abortions would be

1207
01:11:57,229 --> 01:12:01,734
a positive step toward reducing
the number of abortions in America.

1208
01:12:03,152 --> 01:12:06,613
We were able to get George W. Bush
elected with the promise that,

1209
01:12:06,697 --> 01:12:09,783
if we got another ban,
he'd pass it again and sign it.

1210
01:12:11,118 --> 01:12:13,787
And he signed the federal ban into law,

1211
01:12:14,538 --> 01:12:16,040
and it went to the Supreme Court.

1212
01:12:16,123 --> 01:12:19,752
Hey, hey! Hi, ho!
Anti-choice has got to go!

1213
01:12:19,835 --> 01:12:22,796
 The issue of abortion's
before the Supreme Court.

1214
01:12:23,630 --> 01:12:27,343
Justice Sandra Day O'Connor announced
this morning that she will retire.

1215
01:12:28,135 --> 01:12:30,763
Chief Justice William Rehnquist has died.

1216
01:12:30,971 --> 01:12:32,389
The nomination power is one

1217
01:12:32,473 --> 01:12:34,475
of the most serious responsibilities
of a president.

1218
01:12:35,184 --> 01:12:37,436
I will nominate Judge Roberts
to the Supreme Court.

1219
01:12:38,562 --> 01:12:41,065
And Chief Justice Roberts will have
as his colleague

1220
01:12:41,148 --> 01:12:43,108
a proud member of
The Federalist Society,

1221
01:12:43,734 --> 01:12:45,486
Judge Sam Alito, Jr.

1222
01:12:46,862 --> 01:12:50,074
In a 5-4 landmark decision,
the Court's new conservative majority

1223
01:12:50,157 --> 01:12:52,493
today upheld a nationwide ban

1224
01:12:52,868 --> 01:12:55,162
on a procedure critics call
partial-birth abortion.

1225
01:12:55,662 --> 01:12:58,624
In court, an angry
Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg

1226
01:12:58,707 --> 01:13:01,752
took the unusual step of
reading her dissent aloud.

1227
01:13:03,629 --> 01:13:08,300
I strongly dissent from today's opinion.

1228
01:13:09,093 --> 01:13:13,097
The Partial-Birth Abortion Ban Act
cannot be understood

1229
01:13:13,180 --> 01:13:15,682
as anything other than an effort

1230
01:13:16,058 --> 01:13:17,893
to chip away at a right

1231
01:13:18,310 --> 01:13:20,604
declared in Roe v. Wade.

1232
01:13:24,441 --> 01:13:25,776
Roe versus Wade

1233
01:13:26,944 --> 01:13:29,196
prevents us from prohibiting abortion.

1234
01:13:29,363 --> 01:13:30,864
But it does allow us,

1235
01:13:31,865 --> 01:13:33,826
the states, to...

1236
01:13:34,326 --> 01:13:36,453
do some things to protect life,

1237
01:13:36,954 --> 01:13:41,375
if they can show there is
a compelling state interest.

1238
01:13:41,917 --> 01:13:45,421
Governor Rick Perry wanted to end
access to reproductive health care.

1239
01:13:45,838 --> 01:13:48,757
And because the legislature is
so disproportionately

1240
01:13:49,091 --> 01:13:51,301
uh, led by the Republican party,

1241
01:13:51,718 --> 01:13:55,931
they proposed abortion restrictions, which
were the most extreme in the country.

1242
01:13:57,349 --> 01:14:02,146
House Bill 2 was a good example of these
kinds of laws that were being passed in

1243
01:14:02,646 --> 01:14:04,648
many states controlled by the Republicans.

1244
01:14:05,065 --> 01:14:08,527
Laws that really focused
on where the abortion could be performed

1245
01:14:08,819 --> 01:14:13,073
and regulations to either the doctor's
office or a surgical center.

1246
01:14:13,157 --> 01:14:15,534
Thank you for calling
the Southwestern Women's Surgery Center.

1247
01:14:15,617 --> 01:14:17,327
This is Alicia. How may I help you?

1248
01:14:17,411 --> 01:14:19,997
This is what are known as TRAP laws: Targeted Regulation of Abortion Providers.

1249
01:14:23,834 --> 01:14:27,629
And the purpose of these laws is
to make it as difficult as possible

1250
01:14:27,838 --> 01:14:29,214
to provide abortion services,

1251
01:14:29,631 --> 01:14:31,758
prohibit as many abortions as you can,

1252
01:14:31,925 --> 01:14:34,219
make the ones that do occur
as expensive as possible.

1253
01:14:34,303 --> 01:14:35,846
It's so obvious what they're doing.

1254
01:14:37,723 --> 01:14:40,434
My goal is to make abortion,

1255
01:14:40,642 --> 01:14:43,562
at any stage, a thing of the past.

1256
01:14:46,773 --> 01:14:50,152
So these restrictions would shut down
dozens of women's health centers

1257
01:14:50,235 --> 01:14:51,487
all across Texas.

1258
01:14:52,112 --> 01:14:54,323
And that's why Senator Wendy Davis

1259
01:14:54,406 --> 01:14:57,034
decided to stand up and fight
for the rights of women.

1260
01:15:00,037 --> 01:15:01,955
So this bill went to the Senate.

1261
01:15:02,831 --> 01:15:07,336
But, because it was the final day
of the session, the clock was ticking.

1262
01:15:07,878 --> 01:15:11,507
And that gave me an opportunity
for the filibuster.

1263
01:15:11,882 --> 01:15:14,176
Members, I'm rising on the floor today...

1264
01:15:14,384 --> 01:15:19,973
That meant I had about 13 hours of talking
